        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/textView21"
            android:layout_width="370dp"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginStart="16dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="16dp"
            android:layout_marginEnd="16dp"
            android:layout_marginRight="16dp"
            android:text="       Protests have been extremely important in understanding the issues this country faces. In the past, many people did not support protests, as CNN states that in 2016, 18% of people fully supported protests, while 28% supported them partially. Now, both numbers have jumped to 38% and 29% respectively. By race, white people's support for BLM protests have gone from 40% to 61%, 33% to 78% by Hispanic people, and 65% to 86% for African Americans.  The people's voice matters, and if enough choose to speak up and demand a change, there will be one. Especially in the younger generation, there are much louder voices that are pressuring officials to take action. 4 out of 5 people under the age of thirty support BLM, and they are the ones leading these protests. "
            android:textColor="#000000" />

