                android:layout_marginStart="16dp"
                android:layout_marginLeft="16dp"
                android:text="       On May 28, 2020, there were over 8 million tweets related to Black Lives Matter, which is a startling increase from the number of tweets in 2014, which was 146,000. As the new generation becomes more tech-savvy and technology dependent, news will start to spread like wildfire. There have been thousands of videos of proof that show African Americans being beaten and mistreated by police officers, which only fuels the protestors fire. Protests are working and are spreading messages globally, but people must be able to act in the bravery of these protestors and make decisions that will prevent African Americans from ever recieving unfair treatment again.  "
                android:textColor="#000000" />

